.Dd Jun 14, 2000
.Dt CHECK-CONF 1
.Os BIND9 9
.ds vT BIND9 Programmer's Manual
.Sh NAME
.Nm check-conf
.Nd Configuration file syntax checking tool.
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm check-conf
.Op filename
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Pp
.Nm check-conf
is a tool to check the syntax, but not sematics, of the configuration file
for named.
.Pp
The options to
.Nm check-conf
are as follows:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Ar filename
the name of the configuration file to be checked.
If not specified it defaults /etc/named.conf.
.Sh RETURN VALUES
.Pp
.Nm check-conf
return a zero exit value if no errors were detected,
otherwise it returns 1.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr named 8 ,
.Xr RFC1035 .
